 {"id":"bd-1sxo","title":"Implement model_validate() with all options","description":"## Description

Full model_validate() implementation matching Pydantic.

## Python Signature

```python
@classmethod
def model_validate(
    cls,
    obj: Any,
    *,
    strict: bool | None = None,
    from_attributes: bool | None = None,
    context: dict | None = None,
    update: dict | None = None,
) -> Self:
```

## Rust Implementation

```rust
impl<M: Model> ModelValidate for M {
    fn model_validate(
        obj: impl Into<ValidateInput>,
        options: ValidateOptions,
    ) -> Result<Self, ValidationError> {
        // ...
    }
}

pub struct ValidateOptions {
    pub strict: bool,
    pub from_attributes: bool,
    pub context: Option<HashMap<String, Value>>,
    pub update: Option<HashMap<String, Value>>,
}

pub enum ValidateInput {
    Dict(HashMap<String, Value>),
    Json(String),
    Object(Box<dyn Any>),  // for from_attributes
}
```

## Option Behaviors

- **strict**: Strict type coercion (no implicit conversions)
- **from_attributes**: Read from object attributes (ORM mode)
- **context**: Context dict passed to validators
- **update**: Merge these values into result

## from_attributes Behavior

```rust
// Read attributes from another object
let user_schema = User::model_validate(
    db_user,  // Some ORM object
    ValidateOptions { from_attributes: true, ..default() }
)?;
```

